covid_lodging: I’m going in April and tend to use AirBnb and my reasoning is already stated in previous question.
covid_issues: When it comes to AirBnb the only concern was finding the right house because you want to make sure the owner is clean in a time like this but it definitely beats hotel because while a house is one room u have to focus on, u also have multiple rooms in a hotel that have to be cleaned and maintained by staff and at the same time lots of people to be potentially exposed to even with safety measures.

covid_issues:
I wasn’t worried about myself per say, I more so was worried about the possibility of being an asymptomatic carrier and posing a threat to anyone auto immune compromised that I came into contact with. 

There were difficulties with finding things to do considering options were severely limited (understandably so) but inevitably I couldn’t experience the full scope of my environment due to the pandemic.
